<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./style/index.css">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <p class="intro-tag">Welcome to</p>
        <h1>Intro to Backend API</h1>
        
        <div class="info-card">
            <p><strong>This CRUD app</strong> demonstrates basic backend operations using Node.js, Express, and Prisma.</p>
            <p>You can see all the code in this GitHub repo: <a href="https://github.com/khatab1324/IntrobackendCourse" target="_blank">https://github.com/khatab1324/IntrobackendCourse</a></p>
        </div>
        <h2>User Data</h2>
        <p><i>This is all the data we have in our API:</i></p>
        <table class="user-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Username</th>
                    <th>Mark</th>
                    <th>Age</th>
                    <th>Email</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <% data.map(item=>{ %>
                <tr>
                    <td><%= item.username %></td>
                    <td><%= item.mark %></td>
                    <td><%= item.age || 'N/A' %></td>
                    <td><%= item.email || 'N/A' %></td>
                </tr>
                <% }) %>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <div class="api-instructions">
            <h3>API Usage</h3>
            <p>To create a new user, use POST with the following data:</p>
            <div class="code-block">
                {
                  "id": "string (optional - UUID will be generated)",
                  <br>
                  "username": "string (required)",
                  <br>
                  "mark": number (required),
                  <br>
                  "age": number (optional),
                  <br>
                  "email": "string (optional, must be unique)"
                }
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>